WITS Business School has a new head. Dr Sibusiso Sibisi comes from a 14-year stint as president and CEO at the Council for Scientific and Industrial Research (CSIR) where he was credited with building it into a world-class research institution. Sibisi has served on the boards of a number of companies including Harmony Gold, African Rainbow Minerals, Murray & Roberts and currently Liberty and Telkom-BCX. Sibisi obtained his PhD in mathematics from Cambridge University and still has a keen interest in mathematics and finance, an area that the university is looking to grow. He was previously deputy vice-chancellor (research and innovation) at the University of Cape Town. Sibisi was a Fulbright Fellow at the California Institute of Technology in the late 1980s and a senior research associate at Cambridge University in the earlyâ€™90s. He was awarded the Order of Mapungubwe: Silver by President Thabo Mbeki in 2007. National Orders are bestowed on South Africans who contribute to the betterment of the country in their respective fields and represent the highest award that a country can bestow. He starts at Wits in January. thelman@thenewage.co.za